<h2> How to interpret this data in the face of the international scenario? </h2
A reading key could be linked to the positioning of parties (and especially of the PD) about Donald Trump's international activism. Although the latest developments regarding the war in Ukraine are still too recent for producing some effect on the surveys on which today's Supermedia is based, it is not a mystery that the Italian parties have very different positions, on the one hand on the attitude towards the new American administration, and on the other on support to Ukraine. If the proximity to the new American president goes to create a fracture line that basically follows the one between majority and opposition (with Forza Italia and Movimento 5 Stelle that have more “tiepide” positions of the other parties of the respective areas), when we talk about convincingly supporting Kjiv against the Russian invasion we create two cross-fronts: on the one hand FDI, Forza P and center parties, and on the other M5S, Lega and AVS, with its own central position.
In the absence of other elements, therefore, the hypothesis is that the PD can risk losing consent to those parties (such as IV and Action, but also + Europe) that on support to Ukraine, also of military type, have a position much more transient, and of course in open contrast with that expressed, just yesterday, from l<a href="https://www.agi.it/polistrand/news/20 The last Euromedia survey confirms this, according to which 47.8% of Italians do not love Trump's decision-making in foreign policy > (compared with 34.6% that appreciates it) and even 52.1% that believes Trump administration as a "danger" for international stability.
