According to the last projections, however, Musk's explicit support to Alice Weidel's party seems not to be enough to win the elections at the extreme right: Almost certainly, the first party with little more than 30% of the votes will be that of the Christian-Democrats of Friedrich Merz, who will have to seek allies in the new Parliament to obtain a majority and be appointed new Chancellor, but who has already severely excluded any agreement with the extreme right of AfD. But there is no doubt that a surprise result in the German elections could also boost political orientations in other European countries, including – of course – Italy.
