AGI - "The interceptions are made only after the authorization of the judicial authority. Our Department of Penitentiary Administration has never entered into any contract with any company of any kind. No one has ever been intercepted by structures funded by the Ministry of Justice in 2024 and no one has been intercepted by the Penitentiary Police." The Minister of Justice, Carlo Nordio, said this, answering during the question time at the House to a question by Davide Faraone on the case&nbsp;Paragon&nbsp; and the question whether the interception system was used by the Penitentiary Police to intercept journalists.&nbsp;
For the secretary of the Pd, Elly&nbsp;Schlein, "the government &nbsp;Meloni&nbsp; will be remembered as the government of the perennial escape,> samples of the world of dumpbarile with its responsibilities. In fact, after the disturbing release of Almasri, in which Giorgia&nbsp;Meloni&nbsp; it was given to the latitude with Parliament, now the government tries to squeal even on the case&nbsp;Paragon. We know that Italian journalists and activists have been spyed on spyware Graphite, used exclusively by state organs. It is precisely the duty of the government - it has emphasized the leader dem - to clarify and tell us who spyed on these people and for what reason, answer that today the same government refused to give to the questions in Parliament, in which moreover it was asked whether the Penitentiary Police had ever acquired or used&nbsp;Paragon. Before answering this simple question, the undersecretary Mantovano has communicated the classification of this information. What's hiding the government &nbsp;Meloni? The country - concluded Schlein&nbsp;- deserves answers and the place to provide them is the Parliament". &nbsp;
On the case&nbsp;Paragon also intervened Matteo Renzi.&nbsp;"We will ask for access to the documents on the expenses for interception of all the Procures of the Republic. And we do not stop.> We do this because we fought when they violated our privacy with illegal interceptions and illegitimate searches. And then we promised we'd go all the way. We will soon find out who is lying to the Italians - wrote on X the leader of Italy alive. Nordio says in the courtroom that the Ministry of Justice has never entered into contracts with companies that have Trojans. If it is true what the minister says, and we have the duty to believe it, at this point it is evident that in the government someone lies", is another passage of the post published by the leader of Italy alive.&nbsp;
Meanwhile, on the case of journalists and activists spyed also in Italy, through spyware Graphite of the company Paragon Solutions, a complaint against unknown to the prosecutor of Rome is coming. It is the extraordinary initiative of the National Federation of Italian Press and National Order of Journalists, presented during a press conference in the headquarters of the Federation to which the General Secretary Fnsi Alessandra Costante, President Fnsi Vittorio of Trapani, the National President of the Order Carlo Bartoli, the National Secretary of the Order Paola Spadari and lawyer Giulio Vasaturo, who provides union and Order legal support to support the initiative. The complaint, signed at the end of the press conference, will be filed in the coming hours.&nbsp;
"We hope that they are the magistrates to clarify the contours of a case that could have much larger dimensions than those emerged until now - it has premised Alessandra Costante - There was only one spy journalist, Francesco Cancellato? Are we sure? We fear no, > we think that other colleagues have suffered the same fate and there are clues in this regard, starting from Paragon's decision to suspend the contract, as far as the government is concerned." For the General Secretariat of the Fnsi, "the spyware could have been used on a large scale, and to do so could have also been 'lost flies': We want to know, journalists must be free to do their job. The Media Freedom Act, the European Media Regulation, sanctions the prohibition of intercepting, especially with software-spy, chroniclers, if not in cases of exceptional severity: but among the countries that have opposed with more decision to the introduction of this principle there were just Italy and France... What the government doesn't mean, maybe we'll know thanks to a few judges in Berlin."&nbsp;
"We want to know who has been spyed, by whom and why - the President Fnsi, Vittorio Di Trapani has reiterated - it is not tolerable that the secret of State is affixed to a circumstance of this type and that is why we decided to turn to the judiciary, to know what the government does not want to say to the Parliament. The complaint is in the interest not of journalists but of citizens and was an undisputed initiative: the Federation could stay in the window and wait and instead decided to play the game in an attempt to get to the truth. It is very important that with us there is the Order, it is a matter of protecting a fundamental constitutional value such as freedom of information".
"Deleted - said Di Trapani - he knew he was spyed not by authority but by a message Whatsapp: We appeal to all colleagues who received a similar message to say, the Federation is here, at their side." Also for the President of the Order, Carlo Bartoli, "the whole story presents many dark sides, which cannot be clarified. It is the first initiative of the history of this type undertaken by Federation and Order, one does not know who and why he has spyed on one or more journalists, a condition that conflicts with democracy. There can be no state secret about a case like this. After 20 days of contrasting versions we could no longer wait, we would have preferred to make clarity was who had the duty to do so but now we are forced to turn to the judiciary. Paragon is not bought at the supermarket, who and why has spyed Clear and maybe others must come out.> The complaint - Bartoli has concluded - is the final act but we will not spring the grip: We do not defend the privacy of a colleague, but the professional secret and with it the freedom of all citizens".

